# Core Coding Standards

## Naming Conventions

### Files & Components
- Use PascalCase for React components: `LoginModal.jsx`, `UserProfile.jsx`
- Use kebab-case for non-component files: `api.js`, `theme.js`, `auth-store.js`
- Use camelCase for hooks: `useProfile.js`, `useOrderSocket.js`
- Component files should match component name: `Header.jsx` exports `Header`

### Folder Structure
```
src/
├── components/          # Reusable UI components
│   └── ComponentName/   # Each component in its own folder
│       ├── ComponentName.jsx
│       └── ComponentName.module.css
├── hooks/              # Custom React hooks
├── store/              # Zustand stores
├── lib/                # Utility functions
├── app/                # Next.js app directory
└── messages/           # i18n translations
```

### Code Naming
- **Variables & Functions**: camelCase (`userData`, `handleSubmit`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (`UserCard`, `OfferList`)  
- **Constants**: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`API_ENDPOINTS`, `PAYMENT_PROVIDERS`)
- **CSS Classes**: kebab-case (`user-card`, `offer-list`)
- **Props**: camelCase (`isLoading`, `onSuccess`)

## Import Organization

### Import Order
```javascript
// 1. React and Next.js
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';

// 2. External libraries
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';
import clsx from 'clsx';

// 3. Internal components
import Header from '@/components/Header/Header';
import LoginModal from '@/components/LoginModal/LoginModal';

// 4. Hooks and stores
import { useProfile } from '@/hooks/useProfile';
import { useAuthStore } from '@/store/authStore';

// 5. Utilities
import { formatPrice } from '@/lib/adenaFormat';
import { api } from '@/lib/api';

// 6. Relative imports
import './ComponentName.module.css';
```

## Component Structure

### Functional Component Pattern
```javascript
// ✅ GOOD - Clear, organized component structure
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';
import styles from './OfferCard.module.css';

export default function OfferCard({ 
  offer, 
  onPurchase, 
  isLoading = false,
  className 
}) {
  const t = useTranslations('offers');
  const [isExpanded, setIsExpanded] = useState(false);
  
  // Early returns for loading/error states
  if (!offer) return null;
  
  // Event handlers
  const handlePurchase = () => {
    onPurchase?.(offer.id);
  };
  
  const handleToggleExpand = () => {
    setIsExpanded(prev => !prev);
  };
  
  // Render helpers for complex JSX
  const renderPrice = () => (
    <div className={styles.price}>
      {formatPrice(offer.price, offer.currency)}
    </div>
  );
  
  return (
    <div className={clsx(styles.offerCard, className)}>
      <div className={styles.header}>
        <h3>{offer.title}</h3>
        {renderPrice()}
      </div>
      
      {isExpanded && (
        <div className={styles.details}>
          <p>{offer.description}</p>
        </div>
      )}
      
      <div className={styles.actions}>
        <button 
          onClick={handleToggleExpand}
          className={styles.toggleButton}
        >
          {isExpanded ? t('showLess') : t('showMore')}
        </button>
        
        <button
          onClick={handlePurchase}
          disabled={isLoading}
          className={styles.purchaseButton}
        >
          {isLoading ? t('purchasing') : t('purchase')}
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

